id: pm-brief-o4s9
title: "brief: blocked_by edges doubled in blockers/risks (dependencies + blocked_by both parsed)"
description: "extractRelationships parsed a blocked_by edge from BOTH item.dependencies (a blocked_by-kind object) AND item.blocked_by (the denormalized string pm's 'update --blocked-by' writes), emitting the same (from,to,blocked_by) edge twice. Doubled edges inflated blockers[], risks counts, and recommendedPmUpdates. Fix: dedup extractRelationships output by (from,to,kind); no-op for singly-sourced depends_on edges. Regression test added."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[2]: agent-readiness,bug
created_at: "2026-07-14T08:04:59.499Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-14T08:05:12.167Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-14T08:05:12.166Z"
author: claude-opus
acceptance_criteria: brief blockers shows each blocked_by edge once; depends_on edges preserved; unit test covers the denormalized dup case; default output otherwise unchanged.
